<subSubSection id="D446703F95014F91E14A58284B58AD43" pageId="0" pageNumber="201" type="notes">
<paragraph id="1E579DA29C7C5A7D34839BEEE92729D5" pageId="0" pageNumber="201">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5254BE5D2DC80E3C48E89BFA456ECFD9" pageId="0" pageNumber="201">
All the above cited material corresponds to the subspecies 
<taxonomicName id="3BACD08BC64C86E9ED0318BCC263A924" baseAuthorityName="Schulthess" baseAuthorityYear="1923" class="Insecta" family="Vespidae" genus="Ancistrocerus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ancistrocerus biphaleratus subsp. tripolitanus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="201" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="biphaleratus" subSpecies="tripolitanus">
<emphasis id="BA1C74778AC75E8631E088679B100546" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="201">Ancistrocerus biphaleratus tripolitanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(von Schulthess, 1924), a taxon first recorded in the Maltese Islands by 
<bibRefCitation id="A901066B455F94B1C27C41CACABAF004" author="Schembri, SP" journalOrPublisher="Bollettino della Societa' Entomologica Italiana" pageId="0" pageNumber="201" pagination="115 - 116" refId="B17" refString="Schembri, SP, 1985. The Vespoidea of the Maltese Islands: remarks and additions (Hymenoptera Aculeata). Bollettino della Societa' Entomologica Italiana 117 (4-7): 115 - 116" title="The Vespoidea of the Maltese Islands: remarks and additions (Hymenoptera Aculeata)." volume="117" year="1985">Schembri (1985)</bibRefCitation>
which can also be found in Cyrenaica (Libya). However, another subspecies has been recorded from the Maltese archipelago, 
<taxonomicName id="C50AF9981914F214444D4278FAD75C55" baseAuthorityName="de Saussure" baseAuthorityYear="1856" class="Insecta" family="Vespidae" genus="Ancistrocerus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ancistrocerus biphaleratus subsp. triphaleratus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="201" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="biphaleratus" subSpecies="triphaleratus">
<emphasis id="76C52DE8DC7FAEAE0203EF22A4C88F85" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="201">Ancistrocerus biphaleratus triphaleratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(de Saussure, 1855), first by 
<bibRefCitation id="C7E87B0D872F869BF44C543F71FBD928" author="Erlandsson, S" journalOrPublisher="Eos Madrid" pageId="0" pageNumber="201" pagination="11 - 93" refId="B6" refString="Erlandsson, S, 1972. Hymenoptera Aculeata from the European parts of the Mediterranean Countries. Eos Madrid 48: 11 - 93" title="Hymenoptera Aculeata from the European parts of the Mediterranean Countries." volume="48" year="1972">Erlandsson (1972)</bibRefCitation>
, then confirmed by material collected by 
<bibRefCitation id="C026C41051784F7B30345681DFBE2829" author="Schembri, SP" journalOrPublisher="Bollettino della Societa' Entomologica Italiana" pageId="0" pageNumber="201" pagination="90 - 93" refId="B16" refString="Schembri, SP, 1980. Vespoidea from the Maltese Islands (Hymenoptera Aculeata). Bollettino della Societa' Entomologica Italiana 112 (4-6): 90 - 93" title="Vespoidea from the Maltese Islands (Hymenoptera Aculeata)." volume="112" year="1980">Schembri (1980)</bibRefCitation>
. This latter taxon is more widely distributed within Europe, including Iberia, France, Sardinia (Italy), Sicily (Italy) and Greece; it is also found in Northwest Africa and Asia Minor (Carpenter, unpublished). The presence of these two subspecies in Malta was discussed by 
<bibRefCitation id="3330306996D0B7181AB44ECE812C16C7" author="Schembri, SP" journalOrPublisher="Bollettino della Societa' Entomologica Italiana" pageId="0" pageNumber="201" pagination="115 - 116" refId="B17" refString="Schembri, SP, 1985. The Vespoidea of the Maltese Islands: remarks and additions (Hymenoptera Aculeata). Bollettino della Societa' Entomologica Italiana 117 (4-7): 115 - 116" title="The Vespoidea of the Maltese Islands: remarks and additions (Hymenoptera Aculeata)." volume="117" year="1985">Schembri (1985)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
